I have to say, I love the game up until a point. It's fun at first, you slowly build up a knowledge of how to build sturdy bridges and learn a bit how bridges work in real life. About mid-way through though, the challenges are just frustrating. You are barely given enough materials to make the bridge sturdy, so what you end up with is a bridge that just barely works. It also traps you into one particular type of bridge. There's no freedom. On top of that, crashes are frequent.  Possible fixes:   Give the player more (or infinite) materials to work with, but have a par over which the player loses points for each new piece. This would also give more freedom to choose a bridge design.  Add an easier difficulty setting where you're given more materials and/or lower train weight  Increase the sturdiness and rigidity of the materials.
